body:
# Tailwind CSS Configuration

Tailwind CSS has two configuration eras: v3 (JavaScript config) and v4 (CSS-first config). This skill covers both since agents encounter both in the wild.

## v4 Installation (Recommended)

### Vite Plugin (fastest)

```bash
npm install tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite
```

```typescript
// vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from "vite";
import tailwindcss from "@tailwindcss/vite";

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [tailwindcss()],
});
```

```css
/* app.css */
@import "tailwindcss";
```

### PostCSS Plugin

```bash
npm install tailwindcss @tailwindcss/postcss
```

```javascript
// postcss.config.js
export default {
  plugins: ["@tailwindcss/postcss"],
};
```

```css
/* app.css */
@import "tailwindcss";
```

### CDN (prototyping only)

```html
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
```

## v4 Theme Customization (@theme)

All customization happens in CSS via the `@theme` directive:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  /* Add custom colors — generates bg-brand, text-brand, border-brand etc. */
  --color-brand: oklch(0.6 0.2 260);
  --color-brand-light: oklch(0.8 0.15 260);
  --color-brand-dark: oklch(0.4 0.25 260);

  /* Custom font */
  --font-display: "Cal Sans", sans-serif;

  /* Custom breakpoint */
  --breakpoint-3xl: 120rem;

  /* Custom spacing */
  --spacing: 0.25rem;

  /* Custom border radius */
  --radius-pill: 9999px;

  /* Custom animation */
  --animate-fade-in: fade-in 0.3s ease-out;
  @keyframes fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; }
    to { opacity: 1; }
  }
}
```

### Theme Variable Namespaces

| Namespace | Generated Utilities |
|-----------|--------------------|
| `--color-*` | `bg-`, `text-`, `border-`, `ring-`, `fill-`, `stroke-` |
| `--font-*` | `font-sans`, `font-serif`, custom families |
| `--text-*` | `text-xs` through `text-9xl` |
| `--font-weight-*` | `font-thin` through `font-black` |
| `--tracking-*` | `tracking-tight`, `tracking-wide` |
| `--leading-*` | `leading-tight`, `leading-relaxed` |
| `--breakpoint-*` | `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:` |
| `--spacing` | `p-4`, `m-8`, `gap-6`, `w-64` |
| `--radius-*` | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-xl` |
| `--shadow-*` | `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg` |
| `--blur-*` | `blur-md`, `blur-xl` |
| `--ease-*` | `ease-in`, `ease-out` |
| `--animate-*` | `animate-spin`, `animate-bounce` |

### Replace vs Extend

```css
@theme {
  /* EXTEND: adds to existing palette */
  --color-brand: oklch(0.6 0.2 260);

  /* REPLACE: removes all default colors, adds only these */
  --color-*: initial;
  --color-white: #fff;
  --color-black: #000;
  --color-primary: oklch(0.6 0.2 260);
}
```

## v4 Content Detection

v4 auto-detects source files — no `content` array needed. It respects `.gitignore` and skips binaries. Override with `@source`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

/* Add files not auto-detected */
@source "../node_modules/@my-company/ui-lib";
```

## v3 Configuration (Legacy)

v3 projects use `tailwind.config.js`:

```bash
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p
```

```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,html}",
    "./index.html",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        brand: "#4f46e5",
      },
      fontFamily: {
        display: ["Cal Sans", "sans-serif"],
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [
    require("@tailwindcss/typography"),
    require("@tailwindcss/forms"),
  ],
};
```

```css
/* v3 CSS entry */
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

## Debugging: Classes Not Generating

1. **Content paths wrong** (v3): Ensure `content` array matches your source files
2. **Not imported**: Verify CSS file is imported in your app entry point
3. **Dynamic classes**: Tailwind scans statically — `bg-${color}-500` won't work. Use complete strings: `bg-red-500`
4. **Gitignored files** (v4): Use `@source` to include ignored directories
5. **Build not running**: Ensure PostCSS/Vite plugin is configured and dev server is running

## Framework-Specific Setup

### Next.js
```bash
npm install tailwindcss @tailwindcss/postcss
```
```javascript
// postcss.config.mjs
const config = { plugins: ["@tailwindcss/postcss"] };
export default config;
```
Import in `app/layout.tsx`: `import "./globals.css";`

### SvelteKit / Nuxt / SolidJS
Use the Vite plugin — these frameworks are Vite-based.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `NODE_ENV` | Set to `production` for minified output with purged CSS |
